d 'NAAM': module to provide consistent string encoding, ID hashing, and label management
d
d    naam addresses a common and consequential problem in
d large-scale survey and administrative data work: encoding string
d variables consistently across multiple datasets or rounds.
d Stata's built-in encode assigns numeric codes alphabetically
d within each dataset independently. When a new category appears in
d a later round -- a new district, a new industry, a new response
d option -- all alphabetically subsequent codes shift. Any merge or
d append across rounds then produces silently wrong results with no
d error message. This is particularly common in multi-round
d household surveys, administrative panel datasets, and any project
d where data arrives in separate files over time. naam solves this
d by encoding once, saving the exact string-to-numeric mapping to
d an Excel workbook, and reapplying those mappings instantly to
d every subsequent file. The same string always receives the same
d numeric code. New categories are detected automatically, assigned
d the next available code, and the Excel file is updated. The
d workbook also serves as a permanent, human-readable audit record
d of every mapping in the project. 
d
d KW: encode
d KW: value labels
d KW: string variables
d KW: codebook
d KW: Excel
d KW: merge
d KW: panel data
d KW: ID variables
d KW: data quality
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260324
d
d Author:  Vijayshree Jayaraman, NA
d Support: email  jvijayshree26@@gmail.com
d
f naam.ado
f naam.sthlp
